@NODE introduction "Introduction"

		@{b}Introduction@{ub}

Indate is a small program that asks for time&date so if you 
lack a battery-backed-up-clock, it may be very useful.

InDate will save the time & date you enter as a file that at bootup
will be read so that you don't have to change ALL values each time
you reboot your computer.

@ENDNODE

;*************************
;*************************
;*************************
;*************************

@NODE install "How to install"

To install InDate move or copy the program to the WbStartup drawer.

That's it

If you find any bugs, please let me know.

@ENDNODE

;*************************
;*************************
;*************************

@NODE usage "Usage"

Using this program is very simple!

Just enter current time&date and press OK.
If you don't want to save the time you entered, press cancel.

That's it!!

@ENDNODE

